Brittain Brown 9 Yd Run (Austin Parker Kick)
Cam Akers 42 Yd Run (Ricky Aguayo Kick)

videos.description: Florida State's true freshman QB James Blackman finds Auden Tate over the middle for the 20-yard score as the Seminoles score first against the Blue Devils.
videos.headline: Blackman caps 12-play drive with TD pass

videos.description: Duke WR Scott Bracey catches the pass and is leveled at the line-of-scrimmage by Florida State DB Derwin James forcing a punt.
videos.headline: James lays the hammer on third down

videos.description: Florida State QB James Blackman is intercepted by Duke's Mark Gilbert preventing another Seminole score.
videos.headline: Blue Devils take advantage of Seminoles' miscommunication

videos.description: Duke RB Shaun Wilson takes the pitch and throws it deep but the ball is deflected and intercepted by Emmett Rice along the sideline.
videos.headline: Half-back pass backfires for Duke

videos.description: Florida State QB James Blackman steps up in the pocket and takes a hit after delivering a 38-yard pass to a crossing Nyqwan Murray to set up a field goal.
videos.headline: Blackman delivers strike, takes hit

videos.description: On third and long, Duke QB Daniel Jones rolls to his right and delivers a 57-yard dart to T.J. Rahming who makes the diving catch.
videos.headline: Jones rolls right, completes deep pass to Rahming

videos.description: Duke RB Brittain Brown runs nine yards for the touchdown to tie Florida State 10-10 late in the third.
videos.headline: Duke ties game on Brown TD run

videos.description: The Blue Devils' pressure forces Seminoles' QB James Blackman out of the pocket and he throws an interception to Duke's Jeremy McDuffy.
videos.headline: Blackman pressured, throws INT

videos.description: Florida State's freshman running back Cam Akers takes the inside run 42 yards to the house to put the Seminoles ahead 17-10.
videos.headline: Akers eclipses 100 yards on TD run

videos.description: Florida State head coach Jimbo Fisher credits his defense for making crucial stops and says his freshman quarterback James Blackman overcame early mistakes in the 17-10 win over Duke.
videos.headline: Florida State 'growing up' in win over Duke
